===Noun===
'''hussar'''

#Originally, one of the national cavalry of Hungary and Croatia; now, one of the light cavalry of European armies.

Hussar - A word from 15th century Hungary meaning 'one in twenty'. This relates to the conscripting of one man in twenty from every village.
Húsz means twenty in modern hungarian
